editorialSummary.text: Bustling taqueria serving tacos, quesadillas & aguas frescas in a street-style setup (no seating).

originalText.text:
Title: An Authentic Mexican Delight in Grand Central Station - Los Tacos No.1

Los Tacos No.1 in Grand Central Station, New York, surpassed all my expectations with its mouthwatering Mexican cuisine and vibrant atmosphere. From the moment I stepped into this cozy eatery, I knew I was in for a treat.

The authenticity of the food at Los Tacos No.1 is outstanding. Every bite was bursting with flavors that transported me straight to the streets of Mexico. From their perfectly grilled meats to the freshly handmade tortillas, each dish showcases the love and passion that goes into creating genuine Mexican cuisine.

What truly stood out during my visit was the exceptional customer service. The staff at Los Tacos No.1 are not only warm and welcoming but also attentive to every detail. They patiently guide you through the menu, ensuring that each order is prepared to perfection. This level of care and attention further enhances the dining experience.

Despite being located in the bustling Grand Central Station, the speed at which the food is prepared and served is impressive. The efficient service ensures that you can grab a quick and satisfying meal without compromising on taste or quality.

If you're craving an authentic Mexican feast in the heart of New York City, Los Tacos No.1 is an absolute must-visit. With its delectable food, friendly service, and energetic atmosphere, this gem of a eatery is a true delight for anyone who appreciates the flavors of Mexico.

originalText.text: A must go while in New York. Fantastic tacos. Some of the best I've had at a great price point. Fast paced so be ready to order and move. Never had cactus tacos before this place but they were fantastic.

text.text: A must go while in New York. Fantastic tacos. Some of the best I've had at a great price point. Fast paced so be ready to order and move. Never had cactus tacos before this place but they were fantastic.

originalText.text: I got the chicken and marinated pork taco w/Mexican soda on the side. The taco's was very tasty and good. However, this is NYC and I had taco's that is just as good from food trucks or local Mexican eatery. Also, I took a star off from a value stand point. However, if you are in the Grand Central area and hungry then this is a good option. Although, I don't think it is worth a special trip to NYC just for taco's in Los Taco's No. 1.

originalText.text: I've visited their locations many times and they are consistently great. Quick pick up tacos to stand and eat there or takeout. Steak, chicken, pork, or cactus with a few quesadillas options and chips. That's the whole menu. Simple and delicious!

originalText.text: The line is long here as well but waiting time is acceptable. Their quesadillas are simply a delight to try. I would recommend trying the pork and beef steak meat. The place has no seats so it is suitable for a quick bite only.
